  "title": "How can I make an object a Facet?",
  "body": "##### Sample Object:\n\n```\n{\n    \"productName\": 'some product',\n    \"brand\": {\n         \"name\": \"some brand\",\n         \"id\": \"123\",\n         \"url\": \"www.somebrand.com\"\n    }\n}\n```\n\nIs there any way I can make facet like that. I do understand the concept of facet which is not for something like that. But instead of making a separate index I want to keep one index and get the brands that are matched with the product name \n",
